            "Your trekking adventure begins with a drive to Galeshwor (1,170m) along the Kali Gandaki River. After visiting the local Shiva temple, you will start your hike with a steady climb through terraced farmlands. After about 3 hours of walking, you reach Banskharka (1,525m), a charming village famous for its vibrant orange orchards. You will spend the night in a community-run homestay, experiencing authentic Magar hospitality at a comfortable elevation.",
